reviews.review_text:
9-16-78 Did not care for this one too much. The sound seems very muddy and thick. (hard to describe)
I did not listen to the entire show. I listened to the first 3 songs and then skipped around to 4 or 5 other songs to see if the sound would improve. It didn't. i laso thought that the band's performance was rather sluggish. Not sue what it was, but the magic just doesn't seem to be there. While I generally like a good aud over a good sbd, the crowd noise on this one was annoying. I like to hear the roar of the crowd the clapping and cheering but,on most of the tracks I listened to you could hear distinct conversations going on.Not just a few words here and there, but people talking the entire time. I just can't deal with that. It is very distracting. I rate this a 2 at best...I know the MOTB guys did the best they could with what they had to work with, but this one couldn't be salvaged.
Space is the place!  The only thing that made any sense was the space. And being how it was Egypt, well, space is indeed the place! and so, four stars just for that!
